column2: syllabus_text
We are seeking a talented Java Full-Stack Software Developer to join our rapidly growing product team.
The ideal candidate will have strong backend expertise in Java and Spring Boot and solid frontend development experience using React.
You will work on modern cloud-native applications that support critical business functions, collaborating with cross-functional teams in an Agile environment.
Responsibilities: Design, develop, test, and deploy scalable backend services using Java, Spring Boot, and REST APIs.
Participate in all phases of the SDLC, from requirements gathering to production support.
Collaborate with product managers, UX designers, and QA engineers to deliver high-quality features.
3+ years of professional experience in Java and Spring Boot.
2+ years of experience with React.js and frontend development.
Strong knowledge of RESTful APIs, microservices architecture, and JSON.
Experience with SQL and NoSQL databases.
Understanding of Agile methodologies and DevOps practices.
Preferred Skills: Experience with cloud platforms (AWS/GCP/Azure).
Knowledge of GraphQL, WebSockets, or Kafka.
Exposure to Redux, Zustand, or other state management libraries.
You will develop data-rich applications that extract, analyze, and visualize insights from structured and unstructured data sources.
Your work will directly support decision-making systems in industries such as healthcare, logistics, and finance.
Responsibilities: Design and implement backend systems in C# (.NET 6/.NET Core) to support data extraction and transformation pipelines.
Develop ETL jobs and integrate external data sources via APIs, FTP, or web scraping.
Required Skills: Strong experience with C# and .NET Core/Framework.
Knowledge of data mining concepts, clustering, classification, and association rules.
Experience with Python or R for prototyping models is a plus.
Experience in Agile development and using tools like Azure DevOps or Jira.
Preferred Skills: Exposure to big data platforms (e.g., Hadoop, Spark) is a plus.
Knowledge of statistical libraries like ML.NET or Accord.NET.
Experience with healthcare, e-commerce, or fraud detection data.
